&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join our expanding learning and development department, which is a registered provider of apprenticeships.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you enjoy a fast-paced environment where customer service is at the key of all that you do? You will play a vital part in our team that will help to develop the future of Learning &amp; Development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an administrator who can support the Learning &amp; Development Centre and work as part of a larger team of administrators to provide an excellent experience for all our learners and visitors to the Centre. The role is varied with a need for a high level of accuracy, IT skills, diary management, minute taking and the ability to prioritise workloads.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a lot of phone call and face to face queries which makes for a varied workload and no two days are the same.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Personal development is encouraged and is supported through Business Administrator Level 3 Apprenticeships and other relevant IT and administration upskilling courses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Arminda Counter Job title Business Manager Email address arminda.counter@oxfordhealth.nhs.uk Telephone number 07810 756081&lt;/p&gt;
